  "body": "Consider this function:\r\n```solidity\r\nfunction _deploy (bytes memory initCode) internal returns (address deployment) {\r\n  assembly {\r\n    let encoded_data := add(0x20, initCode)\r\n    let encoded_size := mload(initCode)\r\n    deployment := create(0, encoded_data, encoded_size)\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe `deployment` address is assigned a different value depending on whether a call is static or not.\r\n\r\nAccessing the address elsewhere in the call solves the issue:\r\n```solidity\r\nfunction _deploy (bytes memory initCode) internal returns (address deployment) {\r\n  assembly {\r\n    let encoded_data := add(0x20, initCode)\r\n    let encoded_size := mload(initCode)\r\n    deployment := create(0, encoded_data, encoded_size)\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  console.log(deployment);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis issue exists on Hardhat network, but not Ganache.\r\n\r\nIt is reproducible [in this environment](https://github.com/solidstate-network/solidstate-solidity/commit/07f2fb9f463fb089c04c07e0327f570b51fb4125).\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nyarn run compile\r\nhh test test/factory/Factory.ts\r\n```",
